public static int max(int[] arr) {
  int ret = arr[0];
  for (int i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
    if (arr[i] < ret) {
    ret = arr[i];
    }
  }
  return ret;
}

The loop invariant for the max function is that the value of ret is always equal to the 
maximum value of the values that have been traversed so far in the list.
